/getMealsList.ingredients:
• 1 cup green beans, finely chopped
  • 2 cups cauliflower, finely chopped
  • 1 cup carrots, finely chopped
  • 2 medium onions, finely chopped
  • 2 medium potatoes, boiled , peeled, and mashed
  • 1/2 cup green peas(fresh or frozen)
  • 2 medium tomatoes, finely chopped
  • 1 tbsp ginger paste
  • 1 tbsp garlic paste
  • 1-1/2 tbsp Pav Bhaji Masala (you can find this masala in Indian grocery stores)
  • Between 1/2 and 1 tsp chili powder
  • 2 tbsp canola oil
  • lime wedges for garnish
  • cilantro for garnish
/getMealsList.directions:
1. Pressure cook green beans, cauliflower, carrots, and peas with 1 cup water and 1 tsp salt.
  2. Mash the vegetables and mix in the mashed potatoes. Do not grind it into paste. The mixture should be coarse
  3. On medium heat, heat oil in a pan. Add 1/2 of the chopped onions (reserve other half for garnish), ginger and garlic and saute' until soft and translucent.
  4. Add tomatoes, chili powder, and Pavbhaji masala and saute' for 4-5 min.
  5. Add vegetable mixture and saute' for 2 min.
  6. Add some water to make the consistency like chili or thick soup. Adjust salt to taste.
  7. Increase the heat to high, bring to boil, then lower the heat to low and simmer for 15-20 min.
  8. Serve in a bowl topped with some onions, cilantro leaves and lemon wedges. 
  9. Serve along with toasted dinner rolls or burger buns.

/getMealsList.ingredients:
• 1 medium onion, diced
  • 6 ounces Fresh Express Baby Spinach
  • 2 large eggs
  • 1/2 cup egg beaters (liquid substitute)
  • 1/2 cup all purpose flour
  • 1/2 tsp baking powder
  • pinch cayenne pepper
  • 1 1/3 cups non fat milk
  • 1/2 cup feta cheese
/getMealsList.directions:
1. Preheat oven to 400F.
  2. Lightly grease a 10-inch quiche/tart pan (or a pie plate)
  3. In a medium frying pan, cook diced onion with a bit of vegetable oil (or cooking spray) over medium-high heat until translucent and tender.
  4. Add in fresh spinach and cook until just wilted. Set aside to cool for a few minutes
  5. In a large mixing bowl, whisk together eggs, flour, and baking powder. Whisk in milk, then stir in spinach-onion mixture.
  6. Pour quiche base into prepared pan. Top with feta cheese.
  7. Bake for 25 minutes, or until center is set and the outside edge is golden brown.
  8. Let set for 5 minutes, then slice and serve.

/getMealsList.ingredients:
• 1-1/2 cup blanched almond flour
  • 2 teaspoons cinnamon
  • 1 teaspoon baking soda
  • 1/2 teaspoon salt
  • 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg
  • 3 eggs, beaten
  • 1/2 tablespoon honey (more if you want it sweeter, ~1/4 cup)
  • 1 ripe banana
  • 1 cup shredded, unpeeled zucchini (squeeze out excess water)
/getMealsList.directions:
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees Farenheit.
  2. Combine the dry ingredients in a small bowl.
  3. Place the wet ingredients in the bowl of a stand mixer, then beat on medium for 1-2 minutes until frothy and fully combined. Add the zucchini and beat again just enough to incorporate.
  4. Slowly add the dry ingredients with the mixer running, until all of the flour mixture has been incorporated.
  5. Spoon the batter into 2 mini loaf pans. You can also use this batter to make muffins.
  6. Bake for 30-35 minutes until the middle is set and a toothpick comes out clean.

  • Protein: 4.4 g
/getMealsList.ingredients:
Soup

  • 2 teaspoons canola oil
  • 1 large onion, chopped
  • 2 cloves garlic, smashed and chopped
  • 3 stalks celery, chopped
  • 1 yellow bell pepper, chopped
  • 1/2 teaspoon black pepper
  • 1/2 teaspoon dried thyme
  • 1 tablespoon all-purpose flour
  • 5 Russet potatoes, peeled and diced
  • 1 quart homemade or low sodium chicken or vegetable stock
  • 1 bay leaf
  • 1 ear corn cooked or 1/2 cup frozen kernels
  • 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper

Toppings

  • 8 cherry tomatoes, diced
  • 2 Tablespoons plus 2 teaspoons reduced-fat sharp cheddar cheese, shredded
  • 1 head green leaf lettuce, shredded
/getMealsList.directions:
1. Heat a saucepan to medium-low, add the oil, then add the onions once the oil warms.
  2. Sweat the onions for 3-4 minutes (to soften them; you don't want them to brown).
  3. Add the garlic, celery and bell pepper and cook another 3-4 minutes, until the vegetables are tender.
  4. Stir in the flour using a wooden spoon, and cook for 1 minute to remove the raw flour taste.
  5. Add the pepper, bay leaf and thyme, then slowly pour in the stock and the potatoes, stir and cover.
  6. Simmer for 30 minutes.
  7. After 30 minutes, remove the bay leaf and add the corn and cayenne pepper.
  8. Using an immersion blender or food processor, puree the soup until smooth. If you want a thinner soup, add more stock. 
  9. Ladle the soup into bowls.
  10. Garnish each one cup serving with 1 cherry tomato chopped, 1 teaspoon sharp cheese, and 2 tablespoons shredded lettuce.

/getMealsList.name: Pav Bhaji (Indian mixed vegetables)3
/getMealsList.nutritionInfo:
• Total Fat: 3.9 g
  • Cholesterol: 0.0 mg
  • Sodium: 29.4 mg
  • Total Carbs: 21.5 g
  • Dietary Fiber: 4.1 g
  • Protein: 3.3 g
/getMealsList.ingredients:
• 1 cup green beans, finely chopped
  • 2 cups cauliflower, finely chopped
  • 1 cup carrots, finely chopped
  • 2 medium onions, finely chopped
  • 2 medium potatoes, boiled , peeled, and mashed
  • 1/2 cup green peas(fresh or frozen)
  • 2 medium tomatoes, finely chopped
  • 1 tbsp ginger paste
  • 1 tbsp garlic paste
  • 1-1/2 tbsp Pav Bhaji Masala (you can find this masala in Indian grocery stores)
  • Between 1/2 and 1 tsp chili powder
  • 2 tbsp canola oil
  • lime wedges for garnish
  • cilantro for garnish
/getMealsList.directions:
1. Pressure cook green beans, cauliflower, carrots, and peas with 1 cup water and 1 tsp salt.
  2. Mash the vegetables and mix in the mashed potatoes. Do not grind it into paste. The mixture should be coarse
  3. On medium heat, heat oil in a pan. Add 1/2 of the chopped onions (reserve other half for garnish), ginger and garlic and saute' until soft and translucent.
  4. Add tomatoes, chili powder, and Pavbhaji masala and saute' for 4-5 min.
  5. Add vegetable mixture and saute' for 2 min.
  6. Add some water to make the consistency like chili or thick soup. Adjust salt to taste.
  7. Increase the heat to high, bring to boil, then lower the heat to low and simmer for 15-20 min.
  8. Serve in a bowl topped with some onions, cilantro leaves and lemon wedges. 
  9. Serve along with toasted dinner rolls or burger buns.

/getMealsList.nutritionInfo:
• Total Fat: 2.1 g
  • Cholesterol: 2.0 mg
  • Sodium: 63.1 mg
  • Total Carbs: 29.7 g
  • Dietary Fiber: 4.7 g
  • Protein: 4.4 g
/getMealsList.ingredients:
Soup

  • 2 teaspoons canola oil
  • 1 large onion, chopped
  • 2 cloves garlic, smashed and chopped
  • 3 stalks celery, chopped
  • 1 yellow bell pepper, chopped
  • 1/2 teaspoon black pepper
  • 1/2 teaspoon dried thyme
  • 1 tablespoon all-purpose flour
  • 5 Russet potatoes, peeled and diced
  • 1 quart homemade or low sodium chicken or vegetable stock
  • 1 bay leaf
  • 1 ear corn cooked or 1/2 cup frozen kernels
  • 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper

Toppings

  • 8 cherry tomatoes, diced
  • 2 Tablespoons plus 2 teaspoons reduced-fat sharp cheddar cheese, shredded
  • 1 head green leaf lettuce, shredded
/getMealsList.directions:
1. Heat a saucepan to medium-low, add the oil, then add the onions once the oil warms.
  2. Sweat the onions for 3-4 minutes (to soften them; you don't want them to brown).
  3. Add the garlic, celery and bell pepper and cook another 3-4 minutes, until the vegetables are tender.
  4. Stir in the flour using a wooden spoon, and cook for 1 minute to remove the raw flour taste.
  5. Add the pepper, bay leaf and thyme, then slowly pour in the stock and the potatoes, stir and cover.
  6. Simmer for 30 minutes.
  7. After 30 minutes, remove the bay leaf and add the corn and cayenne pepper.
  8. Using an immersion blender or food processor, puree the soup until smooth. If you want a thinner soup, add more stock. 
  9. Ladle the soup into bowls.
  10. Garnish each one cup serving with 1 cherry tomato chopped, 1 teaspoon sharp cheese, and 2 tablespoons shredded lettuce.
